I need to identify the capital contributed by shareholders in exchange for shares from the provided financial statements.

Looking at the balance sheet, I can see the "Paid-in Capital" line item, which represents the capital contributed by shareholders in exchange for company shares.

From the balance sheet:
- Initial Paid-in Capital: 13,000,000.00 on 2023-12-31
- End Paid-in Capital: 13,000,000.00 on 2024-01-29

This shows that the paid-in capital remained unchanged during this period. No additional capital was contributed by shareholders, and no capital was returned to shareholders.
